    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-21T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="235"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-21T12:00:00-07:00"
                            >December 21, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. Your 36, December 20, 1 p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d235fn32">See footnote 29,
                            <ref target="#pg_203">p. 203</ref>.</note> The Guatemalan Government is
                    entirely in agreement with the Department’s point of view and the necessary
                    instructions will be given at once to the Guatemalan Minister in Salvador.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Salvador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
